{
  "page": "House Sarwyck",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #1e90ff;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Mbox notice.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/40px-Mbox_notice.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/60px-Mbox_notice.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/80px-Mbox_notice.png 2x\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <p>This article is about content invented for the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_(2012_video_game)\" title=\"Game of Thrones (2012 video game)\">Game of Thrones</a></i> RPG video game developed by Cyanide Studio. Although this is a licensed derivative work based upon <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A Song of Ice and Fire\">A Song of Ice and Fire</a></i> by <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a>, it is not written by him.</p>\n<p>The material on this page should <i>not</i> be considered canonical for the novels, and is provided for informational purposes only.</p></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\">House Sarwyck of Riverspring</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Sarwyck.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Sarwyck.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a6/House_Sarwyck.svg/250px-House_Sarwyck.svg.png\" width=\"250\" height=\"275\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a6/House_Sarwyck.svg/375px-House_Sarwyck.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/a6/House_Sarwyck.svg/500px-House_Sarwyck.svg.png 2x\" /></a><div style=\"width:100%;min-width:300px;position:relative;z-index:100;border:0 grey solid;margin-top:-3em;margin-bottom:1em;\"><div style=\"display: table; width: calc(100% - 80px); height: 28px; font-size: 12px; line-height: 12px; margin: 0px auto 0px; padding: 0;border:0; position: relative; border-collapse:collapse; text-align: center; font-family: &#39;Uncial Antiqua&#39;; color: #fff; background: #900;\">\n  <div style=\"display:table-cell; vertical-align: middle; padding: 4px; clip-path: polygon(2px 2px, calc(100% - 2px) 2px, calc(100% - 2px) calc(100% - 2px), 2px calc(100% - 2px)); background: #c00;\">Family is Hope, Protect it Always</div>\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; top: -14px; width: 56px; height: 28px; z-index: -3; left: -42px; clip-path: polygon(calc(100% - 2px) calc(100% - 2px), 5px calc(100% - 2px), calc(25% + 3px) 50%, 5px 2px, calc(100% - 2px) 2px, 75% 50%, calc(100% - 2px) calc(100% - 2px), calc(100% - 2px) 5px, calc(75% + 3px) 50%); background: #c00;\"></div>\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; top: -14px; width: 56px; height: 28px; z-index: -4; left: -42px; clip-path: polygon(0 0, 100% 0, 100% 100%, 0% 100%, 25% 50%); background: #900;\"></div>\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; top: -14px; width: 56px; height: 28px; z-index: -3; right: -42px; clip-path: polygon(2px calc(100% - 2px), calc(100% - 5px) calc(100% - 2px), calc(75% - 3px) 50%, calc(100% - 5px) 2px, 2px 2px, 25% 50%, 2px calc(100% - 2px), 2px 5px, calc(25% - 3px) 50%); background: #c00;\"></div>\n  <div style=\"position:absolute; top: -14px; width: 56px; height: 28px; z-index: -4; right: -42px; clip-path: polygon(0 0, 100% 0, 75% 50%, 100% 100%, 0% 100%); background: #900;\"></div></div></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Coat of arms</th><td>\nA broken silver sword on red <i>(Gules, a broken sword argent)</i></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Seat</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Riverspring\" title=\"Riverspring\">Riverspring</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Region</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">Westerlands</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Overlord</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>House Sarwyck of Riverspring</b> is a noble house from <a href=\"/index.php/Riverspring\" title=\"Riverspring\">Riverspring</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westerlands</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The family also owns a manse in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>. They have thus far only been mentioned in the video game <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_(video_game)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Game of Thrones (video game)\">Game of Thrones</a></i>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#House_Sarwyck_at_the_end_of_the_third_century\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">House Sarwyck at the end of the third century</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>Game of Thrones</i></span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Household\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Household</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"House_Sarwyck_at_the_end_of_the_third_century\">House Sarwyck at the end of the third century</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Sarwyck&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: House Sarwyck at the end of the third century\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The known Sarwycks during the timespan of the events described in <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A Song of Ice and Fire\">A Song of Ice and Fire</a></i> are:\n</p>\n<ul><li>no member has appeared yet.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Game_of_Thrones\"><i>Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Sarwyck&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The known Sarwycks appearing in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_(video_game)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Game of Thrones (video game)\">Game of Thrones</a></i> are:\n</p>\n<ul><li>Lord {<a href=\"/index.php/Raynald_Sarwyck\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Raynald Sarwyck\">Raynald Sarwyck</a>}, recently deceased.\n<ul><li>Lady {<a href=\"/index.php/Dorna_Sarwyck\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dorna Sarwyck\">Dorna Sarwyck</a>}, his late wife, died in childbirth.\n<ul><li>Ser {<a href=\"/index.php/Alester_Sarwyck\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Alester Sarwyck\">Alester Sarwyck</a>}, Raynald's eldest son, a <a href=\"/index.php/Red_priest\" title=\"Red priest\">red priest</a> recently living in <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a>. His cause of death is determined by the player's actions.</li>\n<li>{<a href=\"/index.php/Elyana_Sarwyck\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Elyana Sarwyck\">Elyana Sarwyck</a>}, Raynald's daughter, beheaded by Ser Valarr Hill.</li>\n<li>{<a href=\"/index.php/Gawen_Sarwyck\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gawen Sarwyck\">Gawen Sarwyck</a>}, Raynald's second son, slain by <a href=\"/index.php?title=Endrew_(Bloodseekers)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Endrew (Bloodseekers) (page does not exist)\">Endrew</a>.</li></ul></li>\n<li>Ser {<a href=\"/index.php/Valarr_Hill\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Valarr Hill\">Valarr Hill</a>}, Raynald's bastard son and leader of the <a href=\"/index.php?title=Bloodseekers&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Bloodseekers (page does not exist)\">Bloodseekers</a>, impaled on the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a> during a fight with Alester Sarwyck and <a href=\"/index.php/Mors_Westford\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mors Westford\">Mors Westford</a>.</li></ul></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Ryman_Sarwyck\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ryman Sarwyck\">Ryman Sarwyck</a>, Alester's cousin and captain of the guard.</li></ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Household\">Household</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Sarwyck&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Household\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li>Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Harwyn_(maester)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Harwyn (maester)\">Harwyn</a>, counselor, healer and tutor.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Lambert_Weaf\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lambert Weaf\">Lambert Weaf</a>, a servant at the Sarwyck manse in King's Landing.\n<ul><li>{<a href=\"/index.php/Janna_Weaf\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Janna Weaf\">Janna Weaf</a>}, a servant at the Sarwyck manse in King's Landing, wife of Lambert, killed by Valarr Hill.</li></ul></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Hubb\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hubb\">Hubb</a>, a servant at the Sarwyck manse in King's Landing.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Sarwyck&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_(video_game)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Game of Thrones (video game)\">Game of Thrones</a></i></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404023637\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.064 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.234 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 382/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 1972/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 15924/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 907/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 306/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.160/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 5.43 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  221.949      1 -total\n 98.21%  217.978      1 Template:Noble_House\n 97.86%  217.207      1 Template:Infobox\n 12.02%   26.685     10 Template:Infobox_value\n  3.88%    8.609      3 Template:Infobox_label\n  0.70%    1.557      1 Template:Game\n  0.61%    1.365      1 Template:Noble_House/words\n  0.60%    1.340      1 Template:References\n  0.46%    1.018      1 Template:Mbox\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:21197-0!canonical and timestamp 20260404023637 and revision id 310737\n -->\n",
